cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework to learn a mapping from low-to-high resolution endoscopic images using conditional adversarial networks and spatial attention. This involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV and cs.LG sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the resolution of capsule endoscopy images, which involves medical imaging (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper mentions the potential for using computational approaches for polyp detection and characterization, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE sub-category.
